      <to><locator><doc uri="https://github.com/rqml-org/rqml-skill/blob/main/requirements.rqml" docId="RQML-SKILL-001" id="REQ-AUTHORING-CRAFT" title="Canonical authoring-craft reference"/></locator></to>
    </edge>
    <edge id="E-GUARD-UPSTREAM" type="dependsOn" confidence="0.9">
      <from><locator><local id="REQ-CRAFT-GUARD"/></locator></from>
      <to><locator><doc uri="https://github.com/rqml-org/rqml-skill/blob/main/requirements.rqml" docId="RQML-SKILL-001" id="REQ-CRAFT-SYNC" title="Automated craft propagation to plugins"/></locator></to>
    </edge>

    <!-- Sibling reuse: the anchor/validate/gate shape is inherited from the Codex adapter -->
    <edge id="E-SIBLING-CODEX" type="dependsOn" confidence="0.7">
      <from><locator><local id="REQ-ENFORCEMENT-HONESTY"/></locator></from>
      <to><locator><doc uri="https://github.com/rqml-org/rqml-codex/blob/main/requirements.rqml" docId="RQML-CODEX-001" id="REQ-TRUST-TRANSPARENCY" title="Honest enforcement status"/></locator></to>
    </edge>
  </trace>

  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <!-- GOVERNANCE                                                    -->
  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <governance>
    <issue id="ISS-IMPL-ZERO" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Implementation coverage is zero by design at this draft: the spec
        precedes the plugin. Every implements/verifiedBy edge to an artifact
        will be recorded with rqml link as the corresponding piece lands, and
        the drift baseline committed so the gate detects changed implementations
        thereafter.
      </statement>
      <notes>Dogfood baseline, mirroring ISS-IMPL-ZERO in the sibling specs.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-SIBLING-PARITY" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        This repository reuses the anchor/validate/gate shape proven in
        RQML-CLAUDE-001 and RQML-CODEX-001 but adapts it to opencode's
        capability inversion: the hard block moves from turn end to the edit
        boundary, the turn-end check becomes advisory, and CI becomes the
        authoritative gate. Open question: how much of the sibling craft
        (commands, docs structure) can be shared verbatim versus host-specific.
      </statement>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-V2-PLUGIN-API" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Open question: opencode ships a forthcoming v2 plugin API with
        first-class agent, command, and skill registration modules distinct from
        config-hook mutation. When it stabilizes, revisit DEC-COMMAND-SURFACES
        and DEC-CONFIG-HOOK-REGISTER to prefer the supported registration path
        over the semi-internal config hook.
      </statement>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-UPSTREAM-GATE" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Open question: two opencode feature requests — sst/opencode #16626
        (a session.stopping hook with output.stop=false) and #16879 (awaited
        event.sync handlers) — would restore a hard turn-end gate. If either
        merges, revisit DEC-SOFT-TURN-END to upgrade the advisory idle check to a
        real block, while keeping the honest posture as the default.
      </statement>
    </issue>
    <approval id="APR-MAINTAINER" role="RQML Maintainer" status="draft">
      <description>Maintainer sign-off on the rqml-opencode specification.</description>
    </approval>
  </governance>

</rqml>
